    {
      "id": "b7f7d753123a27e51fda134a650e29d4715ba592",
      "author": {
        "_account_id": 597,
        "name": "Sebastien Buisson",
        "email": "sbuisson@ddn.com",
        "username": "sbuisson"
      },
      "date": "2020-03-12 07:58:56.000000000",
      "message": "Patch Set 1: Code-Review-1\n\nPatch https://review.whamcloud.com/37224 was landed to fix sanity-selinux test_21a and test_21b, so they should not be skipped.",
      "accounts_in_message": [],
      "_revision_number": 1
    },
    {
      "id": "29d28a05de389c9755e5253d188f2874fb7d4504",
      "author": {
        "_account_id": 117,
        "name": "Andreas Dilger",
        "email": "adilger@thelustrecollective.com",
        "username": "adilger"
      },
      "date": "2020-03-12 08:23:24.000000000",
      "message": "Patch Set 1:\n\n> Patch https://review.whamcloud.com/37224 was landed to fix\n > sanity-selinux test_21a and test_21b, so they should not be\n > skipped.\n\nSure, except that patch was landed a couple of weeks ago already, and these subtests are still failing regularly, so there appears to be a different problem (maybe exposed once the configuration issue was resulted).",
      "accounts_in_message": [],
      "_revision_number": 1
    },
    {
      "id": "7ce86df7ece8cfc0bd0aebd80ef9f1c282e5a6d7",
      "author": {
        "_account_id": 597,
        "name": "Sebastien Buisson",
        "email": "sbuisson@ddn.com",
        "username": "sbuisson"
      },
      "date": "2020-03-12 09:37:31.000000000",
      "message": "Patch Set 1: Code-Review+1\n\nMy bad, I did not pay attention enough. I think it is ok to skip those 2 tests for now, as sepol is not widely used.\n\nIt is weird that patch https://review.whamcloud.com/37224 managed to pass sanity-selinux test_21a and test_21b multiple times, and now those tests are failing.\n\nOne possibility is that another patch has been landed since then, that disturbs the way we set and update sepol on nodemap ('lctl set_param -P').\n\nAnother possibility, which is more likely IMHO, is that patch https://review.whamcloud.com/37224 only went through sanity-selinux, whereas review-dne-selinux launches sanity and recovery-small *before* sanity-selinux. So we could perfectly imagine a side effect of one of the tests in sanity or recovery-small.\nI will carry out investigations in that way.",
      "accounts_in_message": [],
      "_revision_number": 1
    },
